                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7411: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-05-26T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 26, 1926—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>107. Your telegram No. 226, May 23, 2 p.m. Instructions suggested in second
                    paragraph of your telegram are approved.</p>
                <p>The Department considers it preferable to have Mayer confer with Tredwell only at
                    Hongkong. However, in instructions sent to Tredwell<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d574fn10">Not printed.</note> he is authorized to go to Canton if
                    Mayer so requests. If you consider it necessary you may authorize Chamberlain to
                    go to Canton for conference with Mayer.</p>
                <p>The Department prefers to have Mayer use commercial transportation. If commercial
                    transportation is available, no request will be made of the Navy.<note n="11"
                        xml:id="d574fn11">Mayer left Peking May 31, and his arrival at Canton was
                        reported June 12.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
